  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1616582753193-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1616582753193-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1616582753193-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1616582753193-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1616582753193-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> and <strong>pepper strips</strong> to a baking tray,<strong> </strong>drizzle with <strong>olive oil</strong> and season<strong> </strong>with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 10-15 min or until the vegetables are soft and golden – this is your <strong>roasted onion & pepper</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1616582764550-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1616582764550-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1616582764550-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1616582764550-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1616582764550-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the vegetables are cooking, remove and discard the skin from your <strong>salmon fillet[s]</strong>, then cut into 6 pieces per person</p><p>Add the<strong> salmon pieces</strong> to a bowl, drizzle with your <strong>soy sauce</strong> and give everything a good mix up until they're coated</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1616582772711-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1616582772711-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1616582772711-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1616582772711-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1616582772711-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>cornflour</strong>,<strong> ground smoked paprika</strong>,<strong> cayenne pepper </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>ground cumin</strong> with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> to a plate and stir it all together – this is your <strong>spice mix</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> coated</strong> <strong>salmon pieces</strong> to the plate and gently turn them until they're fully coated in the<strong> </strong>spice mix – these are your <strong>spiced salmon pieces</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1616582790192-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1616582790192-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1616582790192-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1616582790192-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1616582790192-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>spiced</strong> <strong>salmon pieces</strong> and cook, turning frequently for 6-8 min or until crisp and cooked through – these are your <strong>crispy salmon pieces</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1616582808143-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1616582808143-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1616582808143-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1616582808143-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1616582808143-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the salmon pieces are cooking, add your <strong>tortillas</strong> to a baking tray</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 2-3 min or until they're warmed through (alternatively, add them to a plate and microwave for 1-2 min!)</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? Use 2 trays!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Plain-wraps-on-a-bakin-tray-1677584995712-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Plain-wraps-on-a-bakin-tray-1677584995712-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Plain-wraps-on-a-bakin-tray-1677584995712-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Plain-wraps-on-a-bakin-tray-1677584995712-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Plain-wraps-on-a-bakin-tray-1677584995712-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop most of your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks (save a few whole leaves for garnish!)</p><p>Combine your <strong>mayo</strong> with your <strong>white wine vinegar</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>coriander</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>in a small bowl – this is your <strong>coriander mayo</strong></p><p>Wash your<strong> lettuce</strong> and pat it dry with kitchen paper, then shred it roughly</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1616582822174-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1616582822174-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1616582822174-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1616582822174-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1616582822174-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To assemble your Baja-style tacos, divide the <strong>shredded lettuce </strong>and <strong>roasted onion & pepper</strong> between the <strong>warmed tortillas</strong></p><p>Top each tortilla with 2 <strong>crispy salmon pieces</strong> and drizzle with the <strong>coriander mayo</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>reserved</strong> <strong>coriander leaves</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
